The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 BCCI to meet on Twenty20

Mumbai: The BCCIs technical committee, headed by Sunil Gavaskar, would meet in Chennai on January 20 to discuss the ICC rules and regulations on Twenty20 cricket which is to be introduced in domestic circuit in April. 

According to BCCIs chief administrative officer Prof Ratnakar Shetty, the domestic Twenty20 event among all units will be held in the first week of April. 

The board has not conducted any tournament in the slam-bang variety of the game till now though India have already played and won a Twenty20 international on their recent tour of South Africa. The Twenty20 World Championship is scheduled in South Africa in September this year. 

The committee will also review the Ranji points system and recommendation of BCCIs joint secretary MP Pandove to play all Super League ties, semi-final and final at neutral venues from next season. (PTI) 




